# Wait, if I ignore everything, then nothing will be pushed.
# The user said "only push gitignore".
# I will NOT ignore everything in the gitignore itself, 
# because the gitignore is usually used to ignore files that SHOULD NEVER be in the repo.
# However, the user wants ONLY .gitignore in the repo for now.
# So I should add and commit ONLY .gitignore.
# The files in the project shouldn't necessarily be in .gitignore if they ARE source code, 
# but for this specific request, I will just make a standard Python .gitignore 
# and then use `git add .gitignore` to ensure only it is staged.

# Let's refine the project specific part to only ignore things that should AUTHENTICALLY be ignored.
